    "number": 1895,
    "state": "open",
    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "tests: Add regression tests for ec_privkey_import_der() rejecting malformed input",
    "user": {
      "login": "cavdarahmet",
      "id": 223631739,
      "node_id": "U_kgDODVRZew",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/223631739?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/cavdarahmet",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/cavdarahmet/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "`ec_privkey_import_der()` has 8 distinct structural checks that reject\r\nmalformed DER private key encodings (wrong sequence tag, bad length\r\nencoding, wrong version field, bad octet string tag/length, and\r\ntruncation at any point). None of these rejection paths were covered\r\nby any existing test -- only the successful round-trip path was\r\nexercised.\r\n\r\nI fuzzed this function extensively (truncation at every length, single-bit\r\nmutation at every byte position, all under ASan/UBSan) and found no\r\nmemory-safety or logic bugs -- the checks are correct as written. This\r\nPR only adds regression coverage so that a future refactor can't\r\nsilently reintroduce a parsing bug here.\r\n",
